org.pepstock.charba.client.configuration

Class TimeTickHandler

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.pepstock.charba.client.configuration.AxisContainer
      • org.pepstock.charba.client.configuration.AbstractTickHandler<CartesianTimeTick,TimeTickCallback>
        • org.pepstock.charba.client.configuration.TimeTickHandler

  • final class TimeTickHandler
extends AbstractTickHandler<CartesianTimeTick,TimeTickCallback>
    Base object to map an axis tick for TIME axes, CartesianTimeAxis or CartesianTimeSeriesAxis.
    It is also common to want to change the tick marks to include information about the data type.
    To do this, you need to add a callback in the axis configuration.
    If the callback returns null or undefined the associated grid line will be hidden.
    Author:
    Andrea "Stock" Stocchero
